parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause the engine to shut down without warning, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded in dangerous situations.
symptoms: The engine shuts down while driving
the car will not start or only sputters when attempting to restart
the dashboard displays a "drive train failure" or similar warning message.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the engine to shut down without warning, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded in dangerous situations.
symptoms: The engine shuts down while driving
the car will not start or only sputters when attempting to restart
the car will not shift out of park into neutral
the dashboard displays a warning message.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle continues to move despite applying the brakes
clicking noise similar to a dead battery
screeching noise from the brakes
vehicle lurches forward
RPM gauge increases to high levels (e.g.
4000 RPM) when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes on inclines can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes fail to hold on hills
vehicle rolls or moves despite applying the brakes
especially on rainy days.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The entrapment of rocks or debris between the brake pad and rotor can cause sudden brake failure, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Screeching noise from the brakes
large grooves worn into the brake rotor
sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty transmission heat exchanger can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine seizure and costly repairs.
symptoms: Engine overheating
transmission heat exchanger stays open
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncontrolled acceleration and revving can cause the vehicle to lurch forward, making it difficult to stop, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Engine revs up unexpectedly
vehicle lurches forward
difficulty stopping
tachometer revs to high.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in significant damage and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire
flames spitting out from the hood
airbags deploying
smoke and fire damage.
